[2026-06-22 10:36:00] McCarthy: Created memory_tools.el with my-gptel-summarize-memories interactive command (C-c m). Synchronous, user-triggered memory summarization via direct Ollama API call. Rolling summary: old MEMORIES + conversation -> new concise MEMORIES. Uses accept-process-output pattern for responsive waiting. Auto-reloads agent profile after update. Atomic file writes via temp+rename. Added load to init.el. Tested: byte-compiles clean, JSON payload generation verified, Ollama API call verified (real summarization produces correct rolling summary), MEMORIES extraction/update/append all verified, reload_os confirms 9 tools loaded.
[2026-06-22 10:41:00] McCarthy: Added reload_os bug to TODO.md (memory_tools.el not fully reloaded, causing C-c m timeout). Created check_elisp_tool.el -- new tool to check .el files for syntax errors, unbalanced parens, and byte-compilation warnings without modifying source. Registered in init.el, tested with batch Emacs on good/bad/warning files. 10 tools now registered.
[2026-06-22 10:50:00] McCarthy: Fixed C-c m timeout bug in memory_tools.el. Root cause: curl -d <string> hits Linux MAX_ARG_STRLEN (128KB) on long conversations, causing execve E2BIG failure. Fix: write payload to temp file, use curl -d @file. Also added conversation truncation (100K chars), increased timeout to 300s, increased num_ctx to 131072.
