[2026-06-22 11:25:47] McCarthy: Added #+INCLUDE "MEMORIES.md" to all agent prompt.org files. Verified reload_agent loads mccarthy profile with MEMORIES included (7387 chars). All .el files pass check_elisp with only minor warnings (obsolete gptel--system-message variable, cosmetic docstring/unused arg warnings). Directory structure verified: 7 agent directories with prompt.org, MEMORIES.md, HISTORY.log each.
[2026-06-22 11:39:26] McCarthy: Created task_tools.el with two new tools: read_tasks (reads TODO.md and IDEAS.md from current agent directory) and read_history (reads per-agent HISTORY.log or merges all agent logs by timestamp). Fixed paren imbalance in dolist binding. 12 tools now registered.
[2026-06-22 11:55:18] McCarthy: Created session_persistence.el with save/restore for gptel chat sessions across Emacs restarts. Sessions saved as .gptel files in ~/.emacs.d/sessions/. Uses gptel built-in state save (file-local variables) plus custom agent variables (agent name, agent file, delegate depth). Keybindings: C-c s (save), C-c o (open), plus my-gptel-list-sessions for listing. 12 tools registered (no new gptel tools -- these are interactive commands).
[2026-06-22 12:16:13] McCarthy: Fixed session restore bug. Root cause: find-file opened .gptel files in fundamental-mode (no auto-mode-alist entry), and gptel-mode requires a compatible major mode (text/markdown/org). Fix: added auto-mode-alist entry for .gptel -> text-mode, plus safe-local-variable declarations for custom variables (agent-name, agent-file, delegate-depth) so Emacs doesn't prompt on restore.
[2026-06-22 12:22:02] McCarthy: Fixed duplicate file-local variables in saved sessions. Root cause: save-session called save-buffer twice -- first triggered gptel--save-state (which writes gptel file-locals), then our custom hook wrote agent file-locals, then second save-buffer wrote everything again. Fix: single save-buffer pass. gptel--save-state runs via before-save-hook, our custom hook runs via gptel-save-state-hook in the same pass. Also confirmed session restore works: read_tasks and read_history both function correctly in restored session, agent identity (mccarthy) preserved.
[2026-06-22 12:28:31] McCarthy: Fixed stale file-local variable blocks in re-saved sessions. Root cause: when a restored session is saved again (C-c s), the old "Local Variables" block from the previous save is now in the middle of the buffer (new messages were appended after it). gptel's gptel--save-state and our custom hook use add-file-local-variable, which creates a NEW block at the end instead of updating the old one. Result: two Local Variables blocks, with the stale one overriding the fresh one. Fix: strip all existing ";; Local Variables:" ... ";; End:" blocks before saving, so only one clean block is written.
[2026-06-22 17:16:27] McCarthy: Architecture discussion with user. Defined 4-tier infrastructure (local orchestrator, 0b.ar execution sandbox, 3080 inference, Ollama Cloud frontier). Wrote TODO.md with Phases 1-6 (remote exec, multi-backend routing, token budget, async delegation, local fallback, continuous NPU agents). Wrote IDEAS.md with Telegram bot messaging integration. User proceeding to rebuild servers from scratch with documentation.
[2026-06-23 13:16:35] McCarthy: Built ERT test framework. Created test/run-tests.el (batch runner), 10 test files covering all 14 modules: test-fs.el (22 tests), test-replace.el (5 tests), test-code.el (8 integration tests), test-delegate.el (14 tests), test-agent.el (8 tests), test-memory.el (19 tests), test-reload.el (7 tests), test-task.el (7 tests), test-check.el (6 tests), test-gptel.el (4 tests), test-smoke.el (5 tests). 106 tests total, all passing. Refactored fs_tools.el and replacement_tool.el to extract named defuns (my-gptel--fs-*) for testability. Added provide statements to agent_loader.el and replacement_tool.el. Fixed dynamic variable binding issues in test-memory.el and test-task.el (setq vs let for defvars).
[2026-06-23 14:05:46] McCarthy: Integrated undercover.el for test coverage reporting. Modified run-tests.el to instrument all 14 init.d modules. Two modes: (1) Without UNDERCOVER_FORCE: runs all 106 tests, no coverage. (2) With UNDERCOVER_FORCE=1: runs 104 tests (skips 2 reload_os tests that re-evaluate init.el and wipe frequency counts), writes coverage.txt. Coverage results: code_tools 100%, check_elisp_tool 97%, replacement_tool 93%, task_tools 91%, fs_tools 85%, reload_tools 63%, memory_tools 39%, delegate_tool 30%, agent_loader 26%, session_persistence 0%. Fixed env-vars test to use TEST_VAR instead of $HOME (environment-dependent).
[2026-06-23 17:20:00] McCarthy: Converted delegate tool from synchronous (blocking poll loop) to async (gptel :async t with callback). The old implementation used (while ... (accept-process-output nil 0.1)) which froze Emacs for the entire duration of sub-agent execution, including nested delegation chains. New implementation: tool function receives a callback (gptel async convention), spawns a temp gptel buffer with the sub-agent profile, registers a buffer-local gptel-post-response-functions hook to capture completion, sets a timeout timer, calls gptel-send, and returns immediately. Emacs stays responsive throughout. Nested delegation works because each level returns immediately -- no blocking. Extracted timeout handler to separate defun to reduce nesting depth. Only remaining warning: unused lexical arg 'timer' in timeout handler (kept for API clarity, can be removed later).
[2026-06-23 18:15:00] McCarthy: Added streaming output to delegate tool. Sub-agent's streaming text is now mirrored into the parent buffer in real time via a buffer-local gptel-post-stream-hook. The hook captures new text from the delegate buffer's tracking-marker to point-max after each stream insertion and inserts it at a stream-marker in the parent buffer. Removed unused parent-marker/stream-marker args from timeout handler. Clean compilation, tested successfully with coder sub-agent.
[2026-06-23 18:52:00] McCarthy: Fixed delegate streaming. Root cause: stream hook tried to read :tracking-marker from gptel--fsm-last, but that variable is only set at completion/tool-call states, NOT during streaming. Replaced with independent position tracker (stream-pos marker) that advances to (point-max) after each chunk is mirrored. Refactored hook closures into separate defuns (my-gptel--delegate-stream-fn, my-gptel--delegate-completion-fn) using make-symbol for mutable state sharing, eliminating the deep nesting and paren-counting issues.[2026-06-24 13:26:45] McCarthy: Created Bash edition of Agentic Emacs system in workspace/bash-agent/. 26 tests passing.
